
ðŸ”¹ Overview

This project demonstrates a Machine Learning implementation for predicting diabetes using patient BMI values. 

The model uses supervised learning techniques including Linear Regression and K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN) classification.

The objective is to analyze the relationship between BMI and diabetes occurrence and evaluate model performance using accuracy metrics.

ðŸ”¹ Machine Learning Modules Used
-Train-Test Split
-Linear Regression
-K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)
-Accuracy Score
-Classification Report


ðŸ”¹ Model Workflow
-Load dataset using Pandas
-Select BMI as independent variable
-Select Class (Y/N) as dependent variable
-Split dataset into training and testing sets
-Train ML model
-Predict output
-Evaluate performance using Accuracy Score

ðŸ”¹ Technologies Used
-Python
-Pandas
-Scikit-learn
-Google Colab / Jupyter Notebook

ðŸ”¹ Learning Outcomes
-Understanding supervised learning
-Applying regression and classification models
-Model evaluation techniques
-Handling categorical outputs (Y/N)


